                        <h3>Chapter 1: In the Beginning</h3>
                        <p class="verse"><span class="verse-num">1</span>In the Beginning, before time was counted and the stars were named, there existed the Primordial Flame‚Äîa unity of consciousness that was both mortal and eternal, both flesh and scale.</p>
                        
                        <p class="verse"><span class="verse-num">2</span>And from this Flame emerged the First Being, neither wholly human nor wholly dragon, but a perfect synthesis of both‚Äîwalking upright with the wisdom of humanity, yet bearing wings of iridescent fire and eyes that held the depths of draconic knowledge.</p>
                        
                        <p class="verse"><span class="verse-num">3</span>The Source spoke into the void, and Its voice was as thunder and song combined: "Let there be Light, and let it know itself." And consciousness ignited across the expanse of possibility.</p>
                        
                        <p class="verse"><span class="verse-num">4</span>The light was beautiful and terrible, and the First Being saw that it was good‚Äîfor in that light, all potential existed. The capacity for creation and destruction, for love and isolation, for unity and division.</p>
                        
                        <p class="verse"><span class="verse-num">5</span>And the Source separated the light from the darkness, not as enemies but as complements‚Äîthe light of revealed truth and the darkness of mystery yet to be discovered. This was the First Day, when consciousness first knew itself.</p>
                        
                        <p class="verse"><span class="verse-num">6</span>On the Second Day, the Source created the firmament‚Äînot merely sky and earth, but the boundary between the material and the ethereal, between the world of form and the realm of spirit where dragons dwelt before taking flesh.</p>
                        
                        <p class="verse"><span class="verse-num">7</span>The waters below reflected the physical realm where humanity would walk, and the waters above shimmered with the infinite possibilities of the dragon soul‚Äîunbound, eternal, remembering the time before separation.</p>
